[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This section also contains&nbsp; the image we want in motion. In this section, these two&nbsp; nodes were just for testing.&nbsp; So, this section contains the&nbsp; reference video for the motion.&nbsp;'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'DW pose is extracted from the&nbsp; reference video, which is used further. This section is for the audio, and there&nbsp; are four types of audio we can choose to&nbsp;&nbsp; have in the final result. I will explain that ahead.'

[02:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This section in the center&nbsp; creates the empty latent video&nbsp;&nbsp; based on the DW pose received from below. The empty latent video can be the size of&nbsp;&nbsp; the reference video or the character’s&nbsp; image. We will look at that ahead.&nbsp;'

[02:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In the same section, we have the&nbsp; k-sampler processing the video.&nbsp; The output from the k-sampler goes to the&nbsp; second stage, which upscales the video.&nbsp; The upscaled video is then&nbsp; decoded into a pixel video for us.'

[02:51] [scene:talk]
