VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The MX FP8 will work, but I have&nbsp; not tried it on an older card. This distilled LoRA has to be used if&nbsp; you are using the base model of LTX.&nbsp;'

[04:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Next is an IC-LoRA. This Realis dance LoRA&nbsp;&nbsp; was uploaded by Kijai on Hugging Face. The LoRA link has been given above,&nbsp;&nbsp; and this is the file that uses the&nbsp; DW pose to transfer the motion.'

[04:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Next is the prompt, which is&nbsp; connected to the prompt enhancer.&nbsp; Turn this switch to true, and&nbsp; the prompt enhancer should work.&nbsp; The output is visible here. And the&nbsp; same goes into the text encoder below.&nbsp;'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The dual clip loader takes two files, and&nbsp; links to both files are given on the left.&nbsp; The image we want in motion is below, and it has&nbsp; been resized. The resolution you see here works,&nbsp;&nbsp; but there are some sizes that won’t&nbsp; work and will give an error like this.&nbsp;'

[05:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The proportion is set to resize, so the image&nbsp; is resized by maintaining its aspect ratio.&nbsp; In case the character appears small&nbsp; in size due to a large background.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You should change this value to crop.&nbsp; The image will be preprocessed, so that&nbsp; it can be used more efficiently further. The video uploaded here is being resized to 512&nbsp; pixels; you can go even lower, like 448 or 416.&nbsp;'

[05:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then it goes to this DW pose estimator. Which is from a custom node group installed. The pose extracted is then brought back to the&nbsp; given size, which goes ahead in the workflow.&nbsp;'

[05:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The pose extracted is visible here, but if&nbsp; you do not want to install this custom node,&nbsp;&nbsp; then there is a natively supported&nbsp; node below which does the same job.&nbsp;'

[05:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This node will need a safetensor file,&nbsp; which can be found on Hugging Face.&nbsp; The link to the file is given on the&nbsp; left; get the file, make this connection.&nbsp;&nbsp; And you can delete this node if not using it. The DW pose preview will be visible here,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which is saved in a folder named trash&nbsp; inside Comfy UI’’s output folder.&nbsp; I have connected the node to show you the&nbsp; output, and it takes time. On the first run,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it took 150 seconds, but it should&nbsp; be faster on the second run.&nbsp; The difference between&nbsp; these two poses is not much.&nbsp; The pose extracted is then used,&nbsp; along with the empty latent video,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to create the video latent in the IC LoRA node.&nbsp; The resolution of the empty latent video&nbsp; is taken from the DW pose we saw below.&nbsp; But we can also use the image resolution&nbsp; to have the same aspect ratio.&nbsp;'

[06:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This total count is the number&nbsp; of frames we got from the video.&nbsp;&nbsp; The same will be the length&nbsp; of the video in the result.&nbsp;'

[07:05] [scene:talk]
