[07:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The lip sync will work, but remember the&nbsp; character will be restricted due to the DW pose.&nbsp; Make the connection, and&nbsp; the audio file will be used.&nbsp;'

[07:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The third is the empty audio; in case the&nbsp; reference video you are using has no audio,&nbsp;&nbsp; then you have this connected.&nbsp; Otherwise, you will get an error.&nbsp; The fourth option here is about the&nbsp; empty latent audio; connecting this&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[07:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will let the LTX model generate some audio. All this audio is connected to the trim node,&nbsp;&nbsp; or the FPS node, which should adjust&nbsp; the audio to match the video\'s length.&nbsp; When the video is generated&nbsp; from the first k-sampler,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

